const faqs = [
  { q: 'Is the Steelcase Gesture worth the money?', a: 'Yes, if you sit for a living and plan to keep the chair for a decade. The 12-year warranty means the $999 price works out to about $83 per year — cheaper than replacing a $300 chair every three years. If you sit fewer than four hours a day, the Gesture is overkill — see our best ergonomic chair under $500 guide instead.' },
  { q: 'How does the Gesture compare to the Herman Miller Aeron?', a: 'The Aeron is a mesh chair with a more breathable, firmer feel; the Gesture is a cushioned chair with softer, more conforming support. The Gesture wins on armrest adjustability and fits a wider range of body types. The Aeron wins on breathability and design. Both are excellent — see our Herman Miller Aeron review for the full comparison.' },
